9 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
10 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
11 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 250.11 of Title 75, unless there
12 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
13 A. As used in this act:
14 1. “Agency” shall have the same meaning as provided for in
15 Section 250.3 of Title 75 of the Oklahoma Statutes;
16 2. “Obsolete” means expired, unused, void, unenforceable, or
17 not enforced;
18 3. “Outdated” means no longer applicable or pertinent,
19 duplicative with other portions of the Oklahoma Administrative Code,
20 or superseded by other laws; and
21 4. “Unnecessary” means that public health, safety, and welfare
22 are not served by the portion of Oklahoma Administrative Code.
23 B. On January 1, 2028, and on January 1 every eight (8) years
24 thereafter, the permanent rules promulgated by or on behalf of the
