ENGR. S. B. NO. 1316 Page 12

1 J. Prior to submission of permanent rules as required by
2 subsections B through I of this section, an agency shall review its
3 enabling statutes and associated statutes relating to the agency’s
4 powers and duties. Each agency shall prepare a report to accompany
5 its submission of permanent rules. The report:
6 1. Shall include any statutory provisions that are deemed by
7 the agency to be obsolete, outdated, or unnecessary. The report
8 shall include for each identified statutory provision a concise
9 notation as to why it should be repealed or otherwise removed from
10 the Oklahoma Statutes;
11 2. Shall state whether the substantive content in the submitted
12 permanent rules is still necessary and, if it is determined to be
13 necessary, the rationale for such determination;
14 3. Shall state whether necessary permanent rule content would
15 be more appropriately integrated into the Oklahoma Statutes;
16 4. Shall include the frequency with which the substantive
17 content of the permanent rules has been updated in the prior five
18 (5) years and the anticipated frequency of updates in the future;
19 5. May include information regarding additional provisions in
20 statute that are not within the agency’s purview but have been
21 identified by the agency as being obsolete, outdated, or
22 unnecessary; and
23 6. May include information regarding provisions in statute that
24 could be made more concise through legislative action.
ENGR. S. B. NO. 1316 Page 13

1 K. An agency shall electronically submit the report required by
2 subsection J of this section with its permanent rules, prior to the
3 applicable sunset date established by subsections B through I of
4 this section, to the President Pro Tempore of the Senate, the
5 Speaker of the House of Representatives, and the chair of the
6 committee in each house established or designated to review
7 administrative rules pursuant to Section 307.1 of Title 75 of the
8 Oklahoma Statutes.
9 L. Permanent rules submitted to the Legislature pursuant to the
10 provisions of subsections B through I of this section:
11 1. Shall be subject to the review, approval, and disapproval
12 provisions provided for in Section 308 of Title 75 of the Oklahoma
13 Statutes; and
14 2. May be renewed for additional terms of eight (8) years, or
15 fewer, by the Legislature by approval and enactment of a joint
16 resolution.
17 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2026.
